#!/usr/bin/env python
"""
SGA2025-build-catalog: merge the SGA beta catalog, NED cross-match results,
DESI DR1 redshifts, and LVD distances/velocities into a unified per-region
FITS catalog.

Redshift resolution
-------------------
For each galaxy a single "best" DESI spectrum is selected:

  0. Proximity filter: only spectra within --desi-max-sep arcsec of the SGA
     center (TARGET_RA/DEC) are considered, excluding background/foreground
     objects whose fiber happens to fall inside the SGA ellipse.
  1. Deduplicate with ZCAT_PRIMARY=True (DESI's highest-S/N coadd per TARGETID).
  1b. Drop physically implausible spectra regardless of ZWARN:
        SPECTYPE='STAR'            — always wrong for galaxies
        SPECTYPE='GALAXY', Z > 1.0 — redshift too high; always a pipeline error
        SPECTYPE='QSO',    Z > 1.0 — redshift too high for this sample
  2. Prefer SPECTYPE='GALAXY' AND ZWARN=0.
  3. Fall back to ZWARN=0 with any SPECTYPE.
  4. Among survivors, pick the highest DELTACHI2.

     Note: target-bit logic (e.g. BGS_TARGET != 0) could be used to break
     ties before DELTACHI2, but is omitted because secondary-program
     observations are equally valid redshift sources.

  If no spectrum survives all filters, Z_IVAR_DESI=0 (no adopted DESI redshift).

SDSS DR17 spectrum selection
-----------------------------
Quality selection mostly happens upstream in SGA2025-desi-dr1-match --sdss:
that script already restricts matches to "best" extragalactic spectra
(SPECPRIMARY, GALAXY/QSO, clean ZWARNING/ZWARNING_NOQSO) within a small
fixed radius (3.5 arcsec default). Here, Z > 1.0 is additionally dropped as
physically implausible for this sample (mirrors the DESI cut above), then
the closest remaining match (by SEP_ARCSEC) is taken when more than one
falls within the radius. If nothing survives, Z_IVAR_SDSS=0 (no adopted
SDSS redshift). This exists specifically to supersede NED's own copy of
SDSS spectroscopy (see NED_FLAG Z_CENSORED_SDSS in SGA2025-ned-merge): NED
doesn't propagate SDSS's own ZWARNING, so a direct match with real quality
information is preferred.

The adopted redshift (Z) priority is LVD > DESI > SDSS > NED:
  - LVD  when Z_LVD  != 0.  (vlos_systemic / C_LIGHT; Z_IVAR_LVD may be 0.)
  - DESI when Z_IVAR_DESI > 0
  - SDSS when Z_IVAR_SDSS > 0
  - NED  when Z_IVAR_NED  > 0

Z_FLAG bits
-----------
  0x01  Z_FLAG_DISCREPANCY     any two of the measured redshifts (LVD, DESI,
                                SDSS, NED) differ by more than
                                --vdiff-threshold km/s
  0x02  Z_FLAG_NED_SUSPECT     NED is the sole redshift measurement (no LVD,
                                DESI, or SDSS value at all) and NED_FLAG
                                Z_SUSPECT is set
  0x04  Z_FLAG_NED_UNRESOLVED  as above, and NED_FLAG Z_UNRESOLVED is set (no
                                confident replacement was found by
                                SGA2025-ned-merge; the adopted Z may be wrong)
  0x08  Z_FLAG_NED_MISSING     as above, and NED_FLAG Z_MISSING is set (NED's
                                own overview had no default redshift at all;
                                the adopted Z came from SGA2025-ned-merge's
                                RedshiftsOfObject override instead)
  0x10  Z_FLAG_CONSENSUS_OVERRIDE  DESI disagreed with SDSS and NED, which
                                agreed with each other; adopted Z replaced
                                by SDSS's; see below
  0x20  Z_FLAG_AUTO_NED_OVERRIDE  adopted DESI/SDSS Z > --ned-override-zmin
                                was automatically replaced by NED's Z; see
                                below
  0x40  Z_FLAG_VI_REVIEWED     Z/Z_IVAR/Z_REF were set (or confirmed) by a
                                manual VI pass; see --vi-redshifts below

NED_FLAG (carried verbatim from ned-merged-{region}.fits, see
SGA2025-ned-merge) may include Z_SUSPECT (0x08, adopted NED_Z exceeded the
redshift-override threshold there), Z_UNRESOLVED (0x10, no confident
replacement was found), and Z_MISSING (0x20, NED had no default NED_Z at all
and the value was adopted from the full RedshiftsOfObject query instead).
Z_NED/Z_IVAR_NED are used as-is regardless of these bits -- unlike the DESI
GALAXY Z>1.0 cut above, no implausibility filtering is applied to NED
redshifts here. Z_FLAG_NED_SUSPECT/UNRESOLVED/MISSING (above) only propagate
these bits when NED is the sole measurement (no LVD, DESI, or SDSS value),
since DISCREPANCY already covers cases where a second measurement exists to
cross-check against; all three are intended as a signal for targeted visual
inspection, not an automatic correction.

Consensus override
--------------------
DESI always wins normal priority when it has a valid redshift, so it is the
only source that can end up adopted despite being the outlier. When DESI,
SDSS, and NED are all measured for an object, DESI disagrees with SDSS
(> --vdiff-threshold), and DESI disagrees with NED, but SDSS and NED agree
with each other, the adopted Z/Z_IVAR/Z_REF are replaced by SDSS's instead
of blindly trusting priority order. Runs before the automatic NED override
below, and is skipped for objects it has already resolved.

Automatic NED override (--ned-override-zmin)
----------------------------------------------
This sample is overwhelmingly z < 0.3, and NED redshifts have already been
purged of photo-z and SDSS-compiled values (see SGA2025-ned-merge), so a
DESI/SDSS redshift above --ned-override-zmin (default 0.3) with an
independent NED measurement on file is treated as a fiber landing on a
background source: the adopted Z/Z_IVAR/Z_REF are replaced by NED's,
unconditionally (not gated on Z_FLAG_DISCREPANCY -- some genuine mismatches
fall just inside --vdiff-threshold). Runs after the consensus override
above (and is skipped for objects it already resolved), but before
--vi-redshifts, so a VI pass can still override either auto-correction if
needed.

Manual VI overrides (optional --vi-redshifts input)
-----------------------------------------------------
--vi-redshifts points at a VI worksheet CSV (see SGA2025-qa-redshifts),
applied after the normal LVD/DESI/SDSS/NED resolution above, per SGAID, by
its VI_STATUS column: 'discard' zeroes Z/Z_IVAR and blanks Z_REF; 'override'
sets Z/Z_IVAR from VI_Z/VI_Z_IVAR and Z_REF='VI'; 'ok' leaves Z/Z_IVAR/Z_REF
unchanged. All three set Z_FLAG_VI_REVIEWED and clear any other Z_FLAG bits
(the issue that triggered VI is resolved). Rows with a blank VI_STATUS are
skipped, so a partially-completed worksheet can be applied repeatedly.

Z_COSMO (peculiar-velocity-corrected redshift)
-----------------------------------------------
For every object with Z_IVAR > 0, the adopted (heliocentric) Z is converted
to the CMB frame using the standard dipole (Planck 2018: 369.82 km/s toward
RA=167.942, Dec=-6.944 J2000). For v_cmb < 20,000 km/s (roughly the 2M++
reconstruction boundary), pvhub (https://github.com/KSaid-1/pvhub; optional
dependency, see etc/README.md) predicts the peculiar velocity from each
available flow-field reconstruction; Z_COSMO is the CMB-frame redshift with
the mean predicted peculiar velocity removed, and Z_COSMO_IVAR combines the
model-to-model scatter with the measured redshift error in quadrature.
Beyond 20,000 km/s -- outside the reconstructions' domain -- Z_COSMO is just
the CMB-frame redshift, with Z_COSMO_IVAR carried over unchanged from Z_IVAR.
If pvhub is not installed, Z_COSMO falls back to the CMB-frame redshift
(no peculiar-velocity correction) for all objects.

Sentinels
---------
  Redshifts / IVARs : 0.   (Z_IVAR=0 => no measurement; Z=0 means either no
                             measurement or a genuine z≈0 for very nearby galaxies
                             — always use Z_IVAR>0 to test for a valid redshift)
  Other floats      : -1.  (strictly negative, unphysical for dist/separation)
  Integer IDs       : -1
  Strings           : ''   (blank)

  NED_Z_UNC=0 in NED means "error not reported" (common in older catalogs).
  These entries are assigned a nominal Z_IVAR_NED = (1 / NED_Z_NOMINAL_ERR)^2
  rather than being treated as missing.

  DIST_NED_IVAR=0 means either no NED distance or no formal distance
  uncertainty was reported (unlike redshifts, no nominal default is assumed).

Dtype validation
----------------
Every column in the beta catalog is checked against SGA_datamodel; any dtype
mismatch is corrected before writing (known case: REGION int64 -> int16).

Output
------
  {outdir}/SGA2025-{region}-{version}.fits   (EXTNAME='SGA2025')

Examples
--------
  SGA2025-build-catalog --neddir /path/nedquery \\
                         --redshiftdir /path/redshifts \\
                         --outdir /path/output

  SGA2025-build-catalog --region dr11-south --vdiff-threshold 500 \\
                         --desi-max-sep 5 \\
                         --neddir /path/nedquery \\
                         --redshiftdir /path/redshifts \\
                         --outdir /path/output \\
                         --lvd-catalog /path/lvd_comb_all_v1.1.0.ecsv \\
                         --parent-nocuts /path/SGA2025-parent-nocuts-v0.10.fits


SGA2025-build-catalog --neddir=/Users/ioannis/research/projects/SGA/2025/sample/nedquery \
  --redshiftdir=/Users/ioannis/research/projects/SGA/2025/sample/redshifts \
  --outdir=/Users/ioannis/research/projects/SGA/2025/public \
  --lvd-catalog=/Users/ioannis/research/projects/SGA/2025/sample/nedquery/lvd_comb_all_v1.1.0.ecsv \
  --parent-nocuts=/Users/ioannis/research/projects/SGA/2025/parent/SGA2025-parent-nocuts-v0.10.fits

"""
import os
